{{Infobox body of water |name = Botsvatn |native_name = |native_name_lang = |other_name = Bossvatn |image = |caption = |image_bathymetry = |alt_bathymetry = |caption_bathymetry = |pushpin_map = Aust-Agder#Norway |pushpin_label_position = bottom |pushpin_map_caption = Location of the lake |coordinates = {{coord|59.3309|07.2047|region:NO_type:waterbody|display=inline,title}} |location = [[Bykle]], [[Aust-Agder]] |type = |inflow = River Skargjesåni |outflow = River [[Otra]] |catchment = |basin_countries = [[Norway]] |date-built = |date-flooded = |length = {{convert|14.6|km}} |width = {{convert|880|m}} |area = {{convert|5.52|km2|abbr=on}} |depth = |max-depth = |volume = |residence_time = |shore = {{convert|29.22|km}} |elevation = {{convert|530|m}} |frozen = |islands = |cities = |reference = [[Norwegian Water Resources and Energy Directorate|NVE]] }}
'''Botsvatn''' or '''Bossvatn''' is a [[lake]] in the municipality of [[Bykle]] in [[Aust-Agder]] [[Counties of Norway|county]], [[Norway]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yr.no/place/Norway/Aust-Agder/Bykle/Botsvatn/|title=Botsvatn, Bykle (Aust-Agder)|publisher=[[yr.no]]|language=Norwegian |accessdate=2017-03-13}}</ref> The {{convert|14.6|km|adj=on}} long, narrow [[reservoir]] is located just to the southeast of the large lake [[Blåsjø]] and northeast of the lake [[Ytre Storevatnet]]. The lake holds water for the [[Brokke Hydroelectric Power Station]], located in nearby [[Valle, Norway|Valle]] municipality. The water from the lake can flow out into the nearby river [[Otra]], but only when water is released from the dam.<ref name="snl" />
The village of [[Nordbygdi, Aust-Agder|Nordbygdi]] is located on the north shore of the lake, and the village of [[Bykle (village)|Bykle]] is located about {{convert|3|km}} to the east of the lake along the [[Norwegian National Road 9]]. The mountain [[Steinheii]] lies on the south shore of the lake and the mountain [[Strondefjell]] lies on the north side of the lake.<ref name="snl">{{cite web|publisher=[[Store norske leksikon]]|language=Norwegian|url=http://www.snl.no/Bossvatn|title=Bossvatn|accessdate=2010-05-16}}</ref>
==See also== *[[List of lakes in Aust-Agder]] *[[List of lakes in Norway]]
